ENTRY       EC 2.5.1.76                 Enzyme
NAME        cysteate synthase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups;
            Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups (only sub-subclass identified to date)
SYSNAME     sulfite:O-phospho-L-serine sulfotransferase (phosphate-hydrolysing, L-cysteate-forming)
REACTION    O-phospho-L-serine + sulfite = L-cysteate + phosphate [RN:R09530]
ALL_REAC    R09530
SUBSTRATE   O-phospho-L-serine [CPD:C01005];
            sulfite [CPD:C00094]
PRODUCT     L-cysteate [CPD:C00506];
            phosphate [CPD:C00009]
COMMENT     A pyridoxal-phosphate protein. It is highly specific for O-phospho-L-serine and sulfite. The reaction proceeds through a dehydroalanine (2-aminoacrylic acid) intermediate. The enzyme from Methanosarcina acetivorans is evolutionarily related to threonine synthase (EC 4.2.3.1), but the reaction is more similar to that of O-phosphoserine sulfhydrylase (EC 2.5.1.65).
